!JSince the mid-Seventies, when a PDP-10 computer played [32mADVENT[37m,
the first ever adventure game (still alive and kicking nowadays as the
[32mZork[37m series), adventure games have always had a special audience ---
imaginative people who weren't satisfied with Space Invaders (or, today,
Quake). By all appearances, text adventures became extinct at the same time as
the Eighties, only to be replaced by graphic adventures by Sierra On-line,
Lucas Arts and others.!)

!JWhat's not widely known is that new games for [32mInfocom's[37m
(1979-1989) famous Z-Machine are still written today by independent authors.
In fact, the adventure game genre enjoys quite an active group of authors and
gamers. Small wonder: the hardware and software limitations of the Eighties
are long past, leaving the game author free to express their imagination. Some
of the new, free games are real works of art.!)

!JWhat we have here is a collection of such games. The games cover all styles
and tastes, ranging from some of the great classics (now freeware), to games
that won interactive fiction (i.e. adventure game creation) contests in recent
years. Have fun!!)

